<recipe
    xmlns="https://cazzscookingcommunity.github.io"
    xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" 
    xsi:schemaLocation="https://cazzscookingcommunity.github.io ../../xml/recipe.xsd"> 
    
<title>Smart Cookies</title>
<filename>smart_cookies.xml</filename>
<thumbnail>smart_cookies.jpeg</thumbnail>
<category>Snack</category>
<category>Dessert</category>
<category>Breakfast</category>
<diet>Vegetarian</diet>
<diet>EggFree</diet>
<yield>24</yield>
<prepTime>PT15M</prepTime>
<cookTime>PT30M</cookTime>
<comment>c/o Kellogg with cazzie tweaks </comment>
<ingredient>2 cups cereal</ingredient>
<ingredient>2 cups SR flour</ingredient>
<ingredient>1/4 teaspoon bicarbonate soda</ingredient>
<ingredient>1/2 cup brown sugar </ingredient>
<ingredient>150 gms butter melted </ingredient>
<ingredient>Zest one orange </ingredient>
<ingredient>1/2 cup orange juice (1 orange)</ingredient>
<step>Preheat oven to 180C.</step>
<step>Mix all dry ingredients in a bowl and stir through orange zest.</step>
<step>Pour in butter and orange juice, mix until just combined.</step>
<step>Make TBSP balls from mixture and place evenly on lined cookie tray.</step>
<step>Press balls down slightly with the back of a fork.</step>
<step>Place in oven for 20-30 mins or until golden brown.</step>
<step>Once completely cool store in airtight container up to a week.</step>
<step>Freeze extras for later.</step>
</recipe>

